trend_summary: Over two decades, the suburban district remains largely intact: curvilinear residential streets stay constant while commercial and light-industrial strips at the southwest and southeast thicken with new large-roof roofs. Minor infill houses appear on scattered vacant lots. Public facilities expand in the northeast, and overall tree canopy grows, slightly increasing green cover without significant sprawl.
notable_changes: 2-3 new warehouse/retail buildings erected along the southwest diagonal commercial strip.
Large-footprint facility and sports field added near the northeastern school complex.
Scattered residential infill replaces small vacant or wooded parcels within interior loops.
Industrial cluster in the southeast gains extra roofs and paving, supplanting open ground.
Street-side and backyard vegetation matures, enlarging continuous tree canopy.
